sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J64033
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is a variant of the pCASP secretion circuit lacking the chaperone (sicP) for the SptP167 secretion tag.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Dan Widmaier
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This is a composite part with both synthetic and genomic source DNA
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This part was not designed with biobrick standard assembly in mind and might contain scar sequence cutsites throughout.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J64007
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The Tobacco Etch Virus (TEV) protease cleavage recognition sequence. This DNA sequence encodes an amino acid sequence recognized by TEV protease (ENLYFQS) for efficient cleavage. The sequence is flanked by glycines on the ends to increase flexibility and accessibility to the protease. After proteolytic processing the C-terminal fragment retains only an S residue, however by the design of this part it will leave an SG dipeptide which becomes the new N-terminus of the mature polypeptide.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Dan Widmaier
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This part was codon optimized for expression in E.Coli.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J64003
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This coding region is the first 167 N-terminal residues from the SptP effector protein in the Salmonella SPI-1 pathogenesis system. This tag is sufficient when used with sicP (BBa_J64002) to direct a fused heterologous protein for secretion through the SPI-1 system. In the natural system this coding frame overlaps with the 3' end of the sicP coding frame.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Dan Widmaier
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This coding sequence was not designed to conform with biobrick standard assembly.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J64022
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the natural RBS from the sicA chaperone (BBa_J6021) in the Salmonella Type III Secretion System.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Dan Widmaier
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This part was not designed with standard biobrick assembly in mind.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J64001
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The sicA promoter is a regulatory element in the Salmonella SPI-1 secretion system. It controls the expression of secreted effector proteins in the natural system and turns on late. Please reference Temme et al, 2008, JMB for exact dynamics of this promoter and associated feedback mechanisms. This promoter only functions in Salmonella strains containing SPI-1.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Dan Widmaier
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This part can only be used in salmonella strains.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J64004
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This protein coding frame is a Guanine Exchange Factor (GEF) domain from human eukaryotic with point mutations to make it constitutively active. This protein can be secreted at high titer via the Salmonella T3S using the Voigt Lab secretion circuit.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Dan Widmaier
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Human Genomic DNA library clone with 2 point mutations
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This part contains 2 PstI sites and is incompatible with biobrick standard assembly

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: 3x FLAG
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: A 3 repeat FLAG (DYKDDDDK) antigen epitope tag used for marking proteins of interest. Proteins carrying this tag can be easily detected using commercial western blotting reagents.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Dan Widmaier
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This sequence was designed as part of an oligonucleotide primer on each strand then annealed and ligated into the vector.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J64043
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the T1 terminator from the pPROTet 6xHN vector commercially available from Clontech.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Dan Widmaier
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This sequence is not designed with biobrick standard assembly compatibility in mind.
